						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tokumaru wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">This subject is confusing as hell for beginners though, and not essential if one doesn't plan on doing mid-screen vertical scroll splits, so don't feel bad if it doesn't make much sense right now.</div><br /><br />That's why I didn't read that document - since I wasn't doing scrolling, I didn't need to worry about scrolling, right? :D<br /><br />When I said unintuitive, I meant unintuitive based on what I've been using as my bible: <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/PPU_registers" class="postlink">the NESDev wiki page on PPU registers</a>. Lots of registers have sneaky little side effects, and you would expect to show up on a major listing page like this. For example, the page happily tells you how to set the PPU pointer using PPUADDR and gives you an example, but doesn't immediately make it clear that you should clean up after you do it.<br /><br />All of my understanding about the NES comes from simulators, so I'm not quite confident enough to edit the wiki at this moment. After I get less hardware shy, I might try to compile all of the gotchas I encountered and find some appropriate places for them.:)</div>

